# Create a utility otssh, this utility will have below features

- add ssh connect
- list ssh connection
- update/edit ssh connection
- delete/remove ssh connection
- Connect
Examples:
- Add ssh connection
    $ otssh -a -n server1 -h 192.168.21.30 -u kirti (add user kirti to connect
    192.168.21.30 with name server1 with default ssh setting)
    $ otssh -a -n server2 -h 192.168.42.34 -u kirti -p 2021 (add user kirti to connect
    192.168.42.34 with name server2 with port 2022 and default ssh setting)
    $ otssh -a -n server3 -h 192.168.46.34 -u ubuntu -p 2022 -i ~/.ssh/server3.pem
    (add user ubuntu to connect 192.168.46.34 with name server3 with port 2022
    and ssh key file ~/.ssh/server3.pem and default ssh setting)
- List ssh connection
$ otssh -l (This should list the name of all connection added using utility)
server1
server2
server3
    $ otssh -ld (This should list the name of all connection with details added using
    utility)
    server1: ssh user@server1
    server2: ssh -p 2021 user@server2
    server3: ssh -i ~/.ssh/server3.pem -p 2022 user3@server3
- Update/Edit ssh connection (This should update the settings for connection
mentioned after name)
    $ otssh -e -n server1 -h server1 -u user1
    $ otssh -e -n server2 -h server2 -u user2 -p 2022
    $ otssh -ld

- Delete/Remove ssh connection (This should Delete the mentioned connection)
    $ otssh -r server1
    $ otssh -r server2
    $ otssh -ld
    server3: ssh -i ~/.ssh/server3.pem -p 2022 user3@server3
- Connect to server (This should connect to the server mentioned with details
added using utility)
    $ otssh server1
    [ERROR]: Server information is not available, please add server first
    $ otssh server2
    [ERROR]: Server information is not available, please add server first
    $ otssh server3
